der.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20disappointing%20because%20Americans%20want%20to%20be%20relieved%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20ongoing%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20do%20we%20still%20have%20persistently%20high%20prices%2C%20but%20we%20also%20have%20high%20interest%20rates%20and%20we%20have%20an%20economy%20that's%20moderating%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamrick%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20things%20should%20continue%20to%20take%20some%20of%20the%20starch%20out%20of%20prices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20also%20said%20earlier%20in%20March%20that%20there's%20no%20rush%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DPrVun8br9mY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etelling%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20House%20Financial%20Services%20Committee%20that%20cutting%20rates%20too%20soon%20or%20too%20much%20could%20%26quot%3Bultimately%20require%20even%20tighter%20policy%20to%20get%20inflation%20back%20to%202%25.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20see%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20data%20so%20that%20we%20can%20become%20confident%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20looking%20for%20better%20inflation%20readings%20than%20we've%20had.%20We're%20just%20looking%20for%20more%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20rate%20cuts%20won't%20come%20later%20this%20year.%20Nick%20Bunker%2C%20economic%20research%20director%20for%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20told%20BI%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-unemployment-work-labor-market-wage-growth-in-february-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFebruary's%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20published%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20the%20pull%20back%20in%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20growth%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20positive%20trend%20for%20the%20Fed%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20Fed%20can%20feel%20%26quot%3Bthe%20labor%20market's%20holding%20up%2C%