Warren%20Buffett%20hasn't%20asked%20for%20a%20pay%20rise%20in%20over%2040%20years%20because%20he%20wants%20to%20signal%20his%20prudence%2C%20frugality%2C%20and%20devotion%20to%20Berkshire%20Hathaway.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmohamed%40insider.com%20(Theron%20Mohamed)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-salary-greg-abel-wealth-pay-berkshire-hathaway-compensation-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Strange%20but%20true%3A%20Recessions%20make%20us%20live%20longer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Senior%20couple%20enjoying%20a%20relaxing%20float%20in%20a%20pool%20with%20a%20downward%20trending%20stock%20line%20depicted%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20pool%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f209386080194819ff9277%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20reason%20governments%20spend%20so%20many%20taxpayer%20dollars%20digging%20their%20economies%20out%20of%20recessions.%20Families%20lose%20their%20homes.%20Children%20go%20malnourished.%20New%20grads%20spend%20years%20struggling%20to%20get%20their%20careers%20back%20on%20track%2C%20forgoing%20marriage%20and%20kids%20and%20homeownership.%20But%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20research%20suggests%20that%20recessions%20are%20good%20for%20at%20least%20one%20thing%3A%20longevity.%20Puzzlingly%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20economic%20downturns%20actually%20extend%20people's%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20evidence%20comes%20from%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32110%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELives%20vs.%20Livelihoods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20new%20paper%20by%20four%20researchers%20led%20by%20the%20renowned%20health%20economist%20Amy%20Finkelstein.%20They%20found%20that%20during%C2%A0the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20from%202007%20to%202009%2C%20age-adjusted%20mortality%20rates%20among%20Americans%20dropped%200.5%25%20for%20every%20jump%20of%201%20percentage%20point%20in%20an%20area's%20unemployment%20rate.%20The%20more%20joblessness%2C%20the%20longer%20people%20lived%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0especially%20adults%20over%2064%20and%20those%20without%20a%20college%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20mortality%20reductions%20appear%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20economists%20concluded%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20they%20persist%20for%20at%20least%2010%20years.%26quot%3B%20The%20effects%20were%20so%20large%20that%20the%20recession%20effectively%20provided%204%25%20of%20all%2055-year-olds%20with%20an%20extra%20year%20of%20life.%20And%20in%20states%20that%20saw%20big%20jumps%20in%20unemployment%2C%20people%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20report%20being%20in%20excellent%20health.%20Recessions%2C%20it%20would%20seem%2C%20help%20us%20stay%20fitter%2C%20and%20live%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20why.%20The%20economists%20ruled%20out%20a%20lot%20of%20possible%20explanations.%20Laid-off%20workers%20weren't%20using%20their%20free%20time%20to%20exercise%20more%2C%20or%20cutting%20back%20on%20smoking%20or%20drinking%20because%20money%20was%20tight.%20Infectious%20diseases%20like%20influenza%20and%20pneumonia%20kept%20right%20on%20spreading%2C%20even%20though%20fewer%20people%20were%20going%20to%20work%20and%20dining%20out.%20Retirees%20didn't%20seem%20to%20be%20getting%20better%20care%2C%20even%20though%20rising%20unemployment%20rates%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20nursing%20homes%20to%20staff%20up.%20So%20what%20could%20the%20explanation%20be%3F%20How%20does%20higher%20unemployment%20lead%20to%20longer%20life%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20was%20pollution.%20Counties%20that%20experienced%20the%20biggest%20job%20losses%20in%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20the%20economists%20found%2C%20also%20saw%20the%20largest%20declines%20in%20air%20pollution%2C%20as%20measured%20by%20levels%20of%20the%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20PM2.5.%20It%20makes%20sense%3A%20During%20recessions%2C%20fewer%20people%20drive%20to%20work.%20Factories%20and%20offices%20slow%20down%2C%20and%20people%20cut%20back%20on%20their%20own%20energy%20use%20to%20save%20money.%20All%20that%20reduced%20activity%20leads%20to%20cleaner%20air.%20That%20would%20explain%20why%20workers%20without%20a%20college%20degree%20enjoyed%20the%20biggest%20drops%20in%20mortality%3A%20People%20with%20low-wage%20jobs%20tend%20to%20live%20in%20neighborhoods%20with%20more%20environmental%20toxins.%20It%20would%20also%20explain%20why%20the%20recession%20reduced%20mortality%20from%20heart%20disease%2C%20suicide%2C%20and%20car%20crashes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0causes%20of%20death%20all%20linked%20to%20the%20physical%20and%20mental%20effects%20of%20PM2.5.%20Overall%2C%20the%20economists%20found%2C%20cleaner%20air%20was%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20the%20decline%20in%20mortality%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20paper%2C%20along%20with%20other%20research%20into%20recessions%2C%20provides%20an%20important%20reminder%20that%20economic%20growth%20isn't%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20shouldn't%20be%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20only%20measure%20of%20our%20collective%20well-being.%20If%20recessions%20save%20lives%2C%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20corollary%3A%20Boom%20times%20%3Cem%3Ecost%20%3C%2Fem%3Elives.%20An%20economy%20firing%20on%20all%20cylinders%20creates%20more%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20it%20also%20generates%20all%20sorts%20of%20unseen%20but%20harmful%20side%20effects.%20%26quot%3BOur%20findings%20suggest%20important%20trade-offs%20between%20economic%20activity%20and%20mortality%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20conclude.%20That's%20economist-speak%20for%20two%20very%20bad%20choices%3A%20Would%20you%20prefer%20wealth%20that%20kills%20you%2C%20or%20poverty%20that%20keeps%20you%20alive%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20that%20dilemma%20that%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20what's%20known%20as%20the%20degrowth%20movement%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20idea%20that%20the%20gross%20domestic%20product%20doesn't%20provide%20us%20with%20an%20accurate%20read%20on%20human%20progress.%20Sure%2C%20economic%20growth%20provides%20jobs.%20But%20it%20doesn't%20tell%20us%20anything%20about%20the%20health%20of%20our%20children%20or%20the%20safety%20of%20our%20neighborhoods%20or%20the%20sustainability%20of%20our%20planet.%20%3Cem%3EWhat's%20the%20point%20of%20having%20all%20this%20money%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20degrowthers%20ask%2C%3Cem%3E%20if%20it's%20making%20us%20worse%20off%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20sympathetic%20to%20that%20line%20of%20reasoning%20%E2%80%94%20up%20to%20a%20point.%20But%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20actually%20%3Cem%3Eshrinking%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20economy%2C%20as%20some%20degrowthers%20advocate%2C%20is%20a%20good%20idea.%20Lower%20growth%20inevitably%20leads%20to%20higher%20unemployment%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20a%20trade-off%20we%20should%20be%20willing%20to%20accept.%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20Japan%2C%20a%20country%20degrowthers%20often%20point%20to%20as%20a%20model%20for%20slower%20growth.%20It's%20true%20that%20Japan%20is%20politically%20stable%2C%20clean%2C%20and%20safe%20even%20though%20its%20economy%20has%20stalled%20for%2030%20years.%20But%20there's%20something%20about%20long-term%20economic%20stagnation%20that%20saps%20a%20country's%20hope.%20Nothing%20changes%20%E2%80%94%20in%20politics%2C%20in%20culture%2C%20in%20society%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0even%20when%20everyone%20knows%20it's%20bad.%20Without%20realizing%20it%2C%20I%20had%20settled%20into%20this%20national%20inertia%2C%20the%20belief%20that%20nothing%20could%20be%20done.%20It%20was%20only%20in%202012%2C%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20San%20Francisco%2C%20that%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20real%20agency%20over%20the%20direction%20of%20my%20life.%20Everyone%20around%20me%20believed%20they%20could%2