I%20was%20wearing%2C%20and%20my%20brothers%20and%20I%20were%20fine%20with%20driving%20our%20dad's%20old%20'98%20Lincoln.%20We%20had%20an%20Xbox%2C%20and%20I%20was%20eating%20a%20lot%20of%20Chipotle%20with%20my%20friends.%20(I%20drove%20the%20neighborhood%20carpool%20and%20got%20paid%20in%20Chipotle%20gift%20cards%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20was%20awesome.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20more%20does%20a%20teenage%20boy%20even%20need%20at%20that%20point%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20didn't%20really%20talk%20about%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20some%20indications%20that%20we%20were%20rich.%20Our%20family%20took%20really%20nice%20vacations%2C%20but%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20there%20was%20a%20disconnect%20between%20things%20and%20how%20much%20they%20cost.%20I%20just%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20guess%20we're%20in%20Japan%2C%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20both%20my%20mom%20and%20my%20dad%2C%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20was%20a%20relatively%20new%20experience%2C%20as%20was%20raising%20children.%20They%20raised%20us%20in%20line%20with%20how%20their%20parents%20raised%20them%2C%20and%20since%20they%20didn't%20grow%20up%20talking%20about%20wealth%2C%20they%20didn't%20talk%20about%20it%20with%20us%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20nice%20to%20just%20be%20a%20kid%20and%20not%20really%20think%20about%20it%2C%20but%20as%20I%20grew%20up%2C%20I%20started%20feeling%20pretty%20uncomfortable%20that%20I%20was%20in%20a%20wealthier%20family%20than%20any%20of%20my%20peers.%20I%20didn't%20like%20that%20people%20had%20presuppositions%20of%20what%20I%20was%20like%20purely%20based%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20had%20an%20attitude%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-how-billionaire-children-spend-parents-fortunes-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erich%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20too%20much%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20in%20some%20ways%20harmful%20since%20I%20was%20a%20rich%20ki