ay%20a%20role%20in%20mobilising%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20has%20taken%20advantage%20of%20his%20incumbency%20to%20ramp%20up%20the%20pace%20of%20his%20official%20engagements%20in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20opening%20hospitals%2C%20flying%20fighter%20jets%20and%20delivering%20his%20annual%20two-hour%20%E2%80%98State%20of%20the%20Union%E2%80%99-style%20address%20to%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20ensured%20he%20gathered%20nearly%201000%20minutes%20of%20TV%20news%20coverage%20in%20the%20last%20week%20of%20February%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20all%20of%20it%20formally%20relating%20to%20his%20duties%20as%20president%2C%20rather%20than%20as%20a%20participant%20in%20the%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20dwarfed%20the%20television%20coverage%20of%20the%20other%20candidates%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fgolosinfo.org%2Farticles%2F146770%5C%22%3E%C2%A0who%20received%20just%207%20to%2017%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0minutes%20each%20in%20the%20same%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20refusing%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20televised%20election%20debates%2C%20Putin%20has%20further%20starved%20the%20other%20candidates%20of%20relevance.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20electoral%20commission%20campaigns%20to%20encourage%20turnout%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20pressures%20from%20above%20from%20state%20enterprises%20and%20municipal%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20were%20used%20(as%20in%20the%20past)%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1017%2FS004388711400001X%5C%22%3Edrive%20normally%20politically%20apathetic%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20elections%20allow%20the%20regime%20to%20check%20its%20degree%20of%20control%20across%20the%20country.%20Russia%20is%20divided%20into%2083%20regions%20(excluding%20the%20illegally%20annexed%20regions%20of%20Ukraine)%2C%20spread%20across%2011%20time%20zones%2C%20meaning%20that%20steering%20everything%20from%20Moscow%20is%20a%20significant%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20predictability%20of%20the%20overall%20result%2C%20turnout%20rates%20and%20support%20levels%20for%20Putin%20and%20the%20pro-Kremlin%20parties%20generally%20vary%20considerably%20in%20each%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20results%20serve%20as%20an%20examination%20to%20see%20which%20regional%20governors%20can%20best%20demonstrate%20their%20regions%E2%80%99%20loyalty%20and%20mobilise%20their%20support%20bases%20for%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20as%20well%20as%20highlighting%20any%20regions%20where%20there%20may%20be%20above-average%20risks%20from%20opposition%20support%20or%20apathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20serves%20an%20important%20propaganda%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20economy%20on%20a%20war%20footing%2C%20for%20the%20presidential%20administration%20it%20is%20important%20to%20show%20that%20the%20Russian%20public%20still%20backs%20Putin%20and%20that%20Western%20sanctions%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20limited%20success%20on%20the%20battlefield%20is%20not%20affecting%20his%20popularity%20adversely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20whose%20resistance%20to%20Russian%20aggression%20has%20been%20presented%20as%20a%20wider%20fight%20for%20democracy%2C%20has%20been%20forced%20by%20the%20war%20to%20postpone%20its%20own%20presidential%20contest%2C%20providing%20a%20contrast%20with%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20message%20of%20%E2%80%98business%20as%20usual%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20may%2C%20of%20course%2C%20still%20be%20the%20odd%20surprise%20before%20the%20final%20results%20are%20certified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202011%20parliamentary%20election%2C%20there%20were%20widespread%20protests%20at%20perceived%20vote-rigging.%20The%20widow%20of%20the%20late%20Kremlin%20critic%20Alexei%20Navalny%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20funeral%20on%201%20March%20in%20southern%20Moscow%20was%20unexpectedly%20attended%20by%20thousands%20%E2%80%94%20called%20for%20all%20who%20were%20against%20Putin%20to%20turn%20up%20simultaneously%20at%20polling%20stations%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D93hgn6hrzUI%5C%22%3E12pm%20on%20the%20final%20day%20of%20voting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20ramping%20up%20of%20repression%20and%20restrictions%20on%20free%20speech%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20however%2C%20only%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fnoon-against-putin-thousands-russians-turn-out-fulfil-navalnys-last-wish-2024-03-17%2F%5C%22%3Elimited%20number%20of%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20prepared%20to%20take%20heed%20of%20these%20calls.%20Thus%2C%20as%20in%20Soviet%20times%2C%20it%20seems%20we%20are%20effectively%20back%20to%C2%A0%3Ci%3Evybory%20bez%20vybora%3C%2Fi%3E%3A%20elections%20without%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDerek%20S.%20Hutcheson%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%20at%20Malm%C3%B6%20University%2C%20Sweden%20and%20Pro%20Dean%20of%20Malm%C3%B6%20University%E2%80%99s%20Faculty%20of%20Culture%20and%20Society.%20He%20has%20researched%20extensively%20on%20Russian%20and%20post-Soviet%20politics.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710837542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F19140717%2F9623a9383b53f68b50efca903d590894657aa7ece75479e89eadbd82c2fa77b1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-do-autocrats-insist-on-sham-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Vladimir%20Putin%20wins%20yet%20another%20term%20in%20the%20Kreml