es-to-monitor-human-rights-related-development-in-afghanistan-taliban-indra-mani-pandey-4383640%5C%22%3Ebegun%20to%20reconcile%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20a%20variety%20of%20pragmatic%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%20how%20far%20and%20how%20quickly%20should%20India%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20Taliban%20in%20practical%20ways.%20Is%20the%20Indian%20public%20opinion%20ready%20for%20this%2C%20given%20the%20fundamentalist%20Islamic%20character%20of%20the%20Taliban%2C%20their%20brutal%20use%20of%20terror%20to%20gain%20power%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20confidence%20in%20the%20relative%20moderation%20they%20are%20projecting%20currently%3F%20Is%20this%20posture%20simply%20tactical%20because%20they%20have%20to%20gain%20the%20world's%20acceptance%20and%20deliver%20governance%20to%20Afghanistan%20in%20very%20difficult%20conditions%2C%20or%2C%20have%20they%20become%20more%20experienced%20and%20learnt%20lessons%20from%20the%20past%2C%20and%20want%20to%20avoid%20repeating%20their%20mistakes%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESour%20Experience%20With%20Taliban%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20antipathy%20for%20the%20Taliban%20cannot%20be%20ignored.%20They%20have%20been%20seen%20as%20creatures%20of%20Pakistan%3B%20their%20past%20role%20in%20the%20IC%20814%20hijacking%20has%20not%20been%20forgotten%2C%20as%20also%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20allowed%20terrorist%20attacks%20against%20India%20from%20their%20soil.%20Their%20medieval%20Islamist%20ideology%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20regional%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20gained%20power%20in%20Afghanistan%20for%20the%20second%20time%20with%20full%20Pakistani%20backing.%20The%20ISI%20chief%20played%20a%20role%20in%20the%20government%20formation%20in%20Kabul%2C%20making%20Sirajuddin%20Haqqani%2C%20a%20designated%20terrorist%2C%20the%20Interior%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20noted%2C%20however%2C%20that%20after%20assuming%20power%2C%20the%20Taliban%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftaliban-indicated-theyd-be-reasonable-in-addressing-indian-concerns-foreign-secretary-harsh-vardhan-shringla-2529331%5C%22%3Eavoided%20negative%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20India.%20They%20have%20assured%20India%20that%20they%20will%20not%20allow%20Afghan%20soil%20to%20be%20used%20against%20the%20country.%20So%20far%2C%20this%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20case.%20They%20complain%20apparently%20that%20despite%20this%2C%20India's%20narrative%20about%20them%20has%20not%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaliban-Pakistan%20Relations%20Are%20Rough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20their%20relations%20with%20Pakistan%20have%20soured.%20The%20Tehrik-i-Taliban%20Pakistan%20(TTP)%20has%20carried%20out%20operations%20inside%20the%20country.%20The%20Taliban%20have%20refused%20to%20act%20against%20the%20TTP%20as%20requested%20by%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20have%20advised%20the%20latter%20to%20sort%20out%20their%20differences%20with%20the%20TTP%2C%20for%20which%20they%20have%20offered%20help.%20Pakistan%20carried%20out%20attacks%20against%20the%20TTP%20in%20Afghanistan%20once%20again%20on%20March%2018%2C%20eliciting%20strong%20protests%20from%20the%20Taliban%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan's%20hopes%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstrategic%20depth'%20against%20India%20in%20Afghanistan%20have%20been%20belied.%20The%20state%20of%20their%20bilateral%20relations%20has%20deteriorated%20further%20with%20Pakistan's%20expulsion%20of%20nearly%20500%2C000%20Afghan%20refugees%20who%20had%20settled%20there%20years%20ago.%20The%20Taliban%20refused%20to%20recognise%20the%20Durand%20Line%20when%20they%20first%20came%20to%20power%20in%20Kabul%20with%20Pakistan's%20backing.%20They%20are%20doing%20so%20again.%20Pakistan's%20fencing%20of%20the%20border%20during%20the%20Ghani%20presidency%20to%20affirm%20the%20Durand%20Line%20on%20the%20ground%20has%20not%20progressed%2C%20and%20in%20parts%2C%20the%20fencing%20has%20been%20ruptured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20are%20asserting%20their%20independence.%20Pakistan%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20stepped%20up%20economic%20pressure%20on%20the%20Taliban%20government%20by%20exploiting%20land-locked%20Afghanistan's%20dependence%20on%20imports%20from%20Pakistan%20as%20well%20as%20the%20transit%20of%20goods%20through%20it.%20The%20country%20has%20been%20blocking%20traffic%20at%20Torkham%2C%20among%20other%20places.%20This%20is%20critical%20because%20customs%20duties%20on%20such%20goods%20are%20a%20vital%20source%20of%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20making%20up%20almost%2050-%2060%25%20of%20the%20total%E2%80%94for%20the%20Taliban%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20The%20Taliban%20Need%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20why%20the%20Taliban%20minister%20concerned%20visited%20Chabahar%20to%20activate%20this%20alternative%20route%20for%20Afghanistan's%20trade%20traffic.%20India%20had%20been%20promoting%20this%20route%20to%20gain%20access%20to%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20Pakistan%20has%20long%20denied%20to%20India.%20There%20is%20now%20a%20shared%20interest%20between%20India%20and%20the%20Taliban%20government%20to%20loosen%20Pakistan's%20transit%20grip%20on%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20subject%20of%20transit%20was%20mentioned%20in%20the%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20Taliban%20in%20its%20Foreign%20Minister's%20meeting%20with%20the%20visiting%20MEA%20Joint%20Secretary.%20It%20might%20be%20time%20to%20give%20Afghanistan%20more%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20projects%20in%20Afghanistan%20during%20the%20Karzai%2FGhani%20regimes%20were%20spread%20all%20over%20the%20country%2C%20including%20in%20areas%20under%20Taliban%20control.%20These%20projects%20were%20very%20well%20received%20by%20the%20locals%2C%20and%20the%20Taliban%2C%20therefore%2C%20did%20not%20disturb%20them.%20India%20has%20invested%20almost%20%243%20billion%20in%20assistance%20projects%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20earning%20the%20people's%20goodwill.%20The%20Taliban%20want%20India%20to%20continue%20this%20form%20of%20assistance.%20An%20Indian%20technical%20delegation%20recently%20went%20to%20Afghanistan%20to%20inspect%20the%20Selma%20dam%20constructed%20by%20India.%20The%20security%20situation%20seems%20to%20be%20under%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EIndia's%20Assistance%20Projects%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20India%20and%20Afghanistan%20have%20historical%20ties.%20These%20have%20essentially%20been%20with%20the%20Pashtuns%2C%20though%20the%20relationship%20later%20extended%20to%20the%20Tajiks%2C%20the%20Hazaras%20and%20the%20Uzbeks%20when%20India%20supported%20the%20Northern%20Alliance%20against%20the%20first%20Taliban%20government.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20Taliban%20are%20Pashtuns%20does%20not%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20we%20distance%20ourselves%20from%20the%20Pashtuns%20at%20a%20people's%20level.%20It%20is%20argued%20that%20if%20we%20want%20to%20continue%20our%20humanitarian%20assistance%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20Pashtuns%2C%20a%20pragmatic%20modus%20vivendi%20with%20the%20Taliban%20authorities%20in%20Kabul%20would%20be%20required.%20The%20Taliban%20appreciate%20the%20projects%20India%20has%20backed%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20want%20them%20to%20be%20expanded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20international%20level%2C%20India%20has%20to%20remain%20in%20line%20with%20the%20overall%20consensus%20against%20recognising%20the%20interim%20Taliban%20government%20unless%20it%20becomes%20inclusive%2C%20gives%20rights%20to%20women%2C%20respects%20human%20rights%2C%20guarantees%20that%20its%20soil%20will%20not%20be%20used%20to%20commit%20acts%20of%20terrorism%2C%20among%20other%20concerns.%20The%20Central%20Asian%20states%20are%20concerned%20about%20the%20spillover%20of%20Islamic%20radicalism%20from%20Afghanistan%20into%20their%20polities.%20Elements%20affiliated%20with%20al%20Qaeda%20and%20the%20Islamic%20State%20seem%20to%20be%20present%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20though%20lately%2C%20no%20major%20incident%20involving%20them%20has%20been%20reported.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20Taliban%20government%20is%20desperate%20to%20obtain%20formal%20recognition%2C%20and%20hence%20its%20moderate%20stance.%20Individually%2C%20some%20Taliban%20leaders%20may%20even%20want%20to%20give%20women%20some%20basic%20rights%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20education%2C%20but%20they%20have%20to%20defer%20to%20the%20Emir%20in%20Kandahar%2C%20whose%20thinking%20remains%20very%20regressive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20thus%20not%20accorded%20formal%20recognition%20to%20the%20Taliban%20government.%20Its%20%E2%80%9Ctechnical%E2%80%9D%20mission%20in%20Kabul%20is%20manned%20by%20middle-level%20officials%2C%20whereas%20countries%20like%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20Turkey%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20the%20Central%20Asian%20states%20have%20ambassadors%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Other%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20faces%20another%20challenge.%20A%20host%20of%20Afghan%20leaders%20who%20have%20quit%20the%20country%20still%20owe%20allegiance%20to%20the%20overthrown%20Islamic%20Republic%20of%20Afghanistan%20and%20fly%20its%20flag%2C%20not%20that%20of%20the%20Taliban.%20India%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20two%20Afghanistans%2C%20one%20inside%20the%20country%20and%20one%20outside%2C%20and%20find%20some%20sort%20of%20balance%20between%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sum%2C%20India%20cannot%20withdraw%20from%20Afghanistan%20as%20it%20did%20during%20the%20first%20Taliban%20regime%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20country%20is%20an%20important%20geopolitical%20piece%20not%20only%20in%20the%20larger%20geography%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20but%20also%20that%20of%20Central%20Asia.%20China%2C%20which%20is%20already%20present%20strategically%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20is%20dominating%20Central%20Asia%20economically%2C%20is%20extending%20its%20sway%20there.%20It%20has%20strengthened%20its%20presence%20in%20Afghanistan's%20neighbour%20Iran%2C%20too.%20India%20thus%20must%20not%20vacate%20its%20bilateral%20and%20geopolitical%20stakes%20in%20Kabul%2C%20and%20for%20that%2C%20the%20doors%20to%20the%20Taliban%20would%20need%20to%20be%20kept%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710837420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Fb8c4he8s_taliban-government-generic_625x300_14_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhard-realities-is-india-ready-for-a-real-taliban-outreach-5267698%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20cannot%20withdraw%20from%20Afghanistan%20as%20it%20did%20during%20the%20first%20Taliban%20regime.%20The%20country%20is%20an%20important%20geopolitical%20piece%20not%20only%20in%20the%20larger%20geography%20of%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20but%20also%20that%20of%20Central%20Asia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhard-realities-is-india-ready-for-a-real-taliban-outreach-5267698%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhard-realities-is-india-ready-for-a-real-taliban-outreach-5267698%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhard-realities-is-india-ready-for-a-real-taliban-outreach-5267698%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Janhvi%20Kapoor%20on%20her%20bond%20with%20Rihanna%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710837390000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108612434%2Cimg